reviews.review: This place is great!!!! Wonderful food and our service from Kale was the best!!!! We will be back!

This is my second time returning to this location and Brandon R. And Kale V. have exceeded my expectations. They provided excellent service and made sure I was well taken care of! I can't wait to come back next week!

Our experience was simply the best! Just finished breakfast. We were the first ones in at opening. We sat in the bar area. Brandon and Ashton provided an insanely awesome level of service to us!!!We had the seasonal Honey Lemon Blueberry French Toast and the Fried Stake Benedict. The food was phenomenal! The Salted Carmel and Vanilla Cream spiked coffees ROCKED!But back to Brandon and Ashton. I think Brandon was training Ashton. He did a really great job talking her through processes and offered pointers. Even as they were working together  neither of them missed a beat in the service they offered. I have worked in Customer Service all my life. I am the head of Customer Success at my company. If I had positions open on my team  I'd have offered them both positions on the spot!Brandon gets bonus points for the Kingdom Hearts reference. A+ service all the way!

I first want to start that if you do decide to come here... come on a weekday or very early on a Sunday. We mafmde the mistake on coming Sunday and waiting over an hour when the hostess stated 30 to 40 minutes. They decided that a large group of people were more precedent to sit before smaller groups. Beside that yhe food here is great. We had the apple fritter French toast. This you have to order if you have a sweet tooth. Very good. My wife had eggs Benedict which she stated was yummy!I would decently come back no problem. But only when I know we are not going to wait half the day for a table .

The ambiance is really nice  good classic music and a friendly atmosphere. Our Server Rosa was attentive with excellent personality. I ordered the Madi Gra omelette with grits & English muffin. We also ordered the fluffy buttermilk pancakes with sausage links & scrambled The food was served heat hot and oh so so so so good. The chef was AWSOME! He introduced himself and began to tell us about the restaurant's in various area's also the other States. We're here from Sacramento  California hopefully you will consider opening a restaurant there or Elk Grove. We will be back.

First timers here today. Wow! What a delight! Francis our server was totally on top of our order and drinks. I had the biscuits and gravy with a side of the freshest tomatoes. Yum! My husband had the power bowl. Was fabulous. A very relaxed atmosphere and social as well. Will be back for sure.

First time at this new location. The restaurant is bright and cheery like a good breakfast place should be. Our server  Kale  was delightful and attentive. My friend ordered the seasonal Honey Lemon Blueberry French toast and said it was delicious. My gluten-free lemon blueberry goat cheese pancakes were also delicious. I love th tartness of the goat cheese with the sweetness of pancakes. Scrambled eggs were good. The sausage is made in house  and is free-formed  so don't expect perfect circles. It has a nice herbaceous quality that was unique and enjoyable. I usually get their baked bacon  so this was a departure for me. I got the strawberry mimosa for the first time. It was good  if a little sweet for me  and definitely spoke of summer. If you visit this location  ask to be seated in Kale's section. You won't be disappointed.

This location has only been open for two weeks  so when my BF wanted to check it out this morning  I allowed my arm to be twisted.It's in the middle of the oddly empty LINC shopping center  next to the Peruvian place. Plenty of parking  which these days is a big plus as far as I'm concerned. The interior is bright and welcoming  with mix of tables and booths.At 8 am this weekday morning it was fairly empty--no surprise for such a new place. The service was fast and friendly  the menu nearly overwhelming. Entrees range from $12-18.I love that he had a choice of teas and I could choose regular or dark roast coffee. Choosing an entree was hard with so many classic or unusual options.  The owner came by to chat  and to bring us a sample of their Biscuit Beignets  which are a delightful cross between the two  served with a very good marmalade.BF went for the Country Fried Steak Benedict  while I got the Country Power Bowl. Both arrived looking great. He declared his side of potatoes "uninspired " and after I had a taste  I agree. They needed to be a bit crispier  I think.But the Bennie was very good  he said. The underlying biscuit was huge  the CFS unusually "delicate " and the Red Eye gravy spot on.My Power Bowl was wonderful start to finish--in fact  I had to take half of it home  and I have a big appetite. The biscuit  which seems to be a specialty of theirs  was perfect  and BIG. Gravy was also just right  as was the side of bacon. And I don't know what sweet ham they put in that scramble  but  DAMN!This place definitely goes on our repeat list  and I suspect it will be a hit once the brunch crowd discovers it.

Stumbled across this spot while in the shopping center and figured we'd give it a go! Very lowkey spot  and solid. The menu was a bit overwhelming (but in the best way possible). So many different things sounded amazing  so we'll definitely have to go back and try some other things!
New location!!! Shrimps and Grits are Amazing! Staff is the BEST!! WOW! Check them OUT!! Hats off to the new Server SETH you did a terrific job young Man.

reviews.review: Great food and service! Took my Peruvian friend here and he approved!There's a Happy Lemon boba shop behind this place as well so it's a win win situation!

Little further north in Austin  but if you're looking for something different this Peruvian spot def was worth a try! They had so many different options in the menu and I look forward to coming back and trying the other options they had.We got a steak empanada & it was delightful! Very light and airy. The dough was a little in the sweeter side but the inside steak evened it out with the savory salty side.Ceviche mixto was worth the $$! Such great flavors and they do not skimp out on the portion!!! Also ordered the Aji de gallina- the flavors were very good! Reminded me of an Indian curry with similar spices. The rice was also so yummy! The chicken was a little in the drier side - looked Kike shredded chicken breast. Potato's we're cooked perfectly. Had a friend get the lomo saltado limeno & said it was good! The meat gave me a Mongolian beef Smokey taste.

We arrived right before the rush. Since it was a nice night we sat outside. Clean and spacious.First appetizer - 6.5/10 - taste was pretty good  probably would have been a lot better if it was hot. We didn't expect it to be cold. It gave potato chicken salad flavors. The white sauce on the plate was really tasty. Chicken empanada - a bit disappointed since the empanada was mostly air (see picture). We couldn't really taste chicken flavor however the meat was very seasoned. Arros con pollo - 4.5/10 - rice was decent. The chicken had a lot of skin. The flavor of the chicken was very bland. Peruvian fried rice - 7/10 - played it safe and got fried rice. Didn't get any Peruvian flavor vibes just fried rice. Was a tad greasy. We didn't order any alcoholic drinks  just waters. I wonder if this was the reason the waiters didn't check on us much to see if we needed anything during our meal. There were other tables outside drinking alcoholic beverages that the waiters seems to visit often during their meal. Nonetheless this will be a "one and done" for me.

Very solid Peruvian food  and I'm so glad that they are here in Austin - we definitely don't have enough. That said  not quite five stars yet for me  but will for sure be back and try more things from the menu. Ceviche: loved this! Good portion size  very fresh fish. Will get again.Sweet plantains: nothing to complain about here: again a good portion size. Nice ripe plantains  slight crisp on outside  soft in the middle. Will get again.Arroz con mariscos: The seafood is very good - it was all tender  perfectly cooked and a good amount of it. But I was less enthused about the rice which was a little lacking in flavor and much too wet. This I probably wouldn't get again. Alfajore: very very good. Fairly thin cookie  delicious dulce de lche filling. Always love these.

After a going away party at Easy Tiger  we stopped into Lima Criolla for dinner. We had a great experience. Knowledgeable and service-oriented server who suggested several fan favorites. We settled on splitting Anticuchos (Grill Beef Hearts Kebab) and Arroz Chaufa de Mariscos (seafood on rice). Both were excellent  Even with two people splitting an appetizer and entree  we had enough leftovers for lunch the following day. Can't wait to return for Ceviche. This is a nice change of pace and a great neighborhood spot. We will be back! Thank you!
HorribleNasty had roaches crawling out my drink rat on the floor like eewwwwewwwwwww

Reviewed this location about a year ago. Visit this location about once a month  but something has changed. I'm not talking about the "post Covid conversions all restaurants have gone though lately (smaller portions/price increases) I'm talking about the flavor. My wife and father in law  both born in Peru  use to love this place  pre Covid. Great quality of meat and the flavor was very authentic. Today  the "Arroz Chaufa" was way over seasoned. Too much salt and the chicken was very overcooked. The larger shrimp portions has been reduced to three over cooked shrimp placed right on top. Folks  shrimp is supposed to be tender on the inside  not rubbery. The "Lome Saltado"  a signature dish of any good Peruvian restaurant was not the same  but to make matters worse  it was drowning in overcooked green onion stalks. I've never seen this dish prepared this way. I've had this meal many times in Lima Peru  and it's not served this way  with so many green onions. The green onions overwhelmed the meal. It robbed the flavor from the few tomatoes and red onions you threw in. Then we played pick out the excess green onion from our meals. My wife enjoyed the Jalea  yet she noticed a lot less medium size shrimp and a whole lot of smaller shrimp. Ok  "Lima Criollo"  let's get back to basic. Consistency! Consistency! Consistency! Balanced seasoning  a reasonable amount of garnish and please taste your food before serving. You have already increased the prices  so please give us what we're paying for. We have always loved your Peruvian authenticity  but you missing the mark with the new changes. Michael C. - Georgetown

I was really looking forward to this place...the ceviche was really good  but otherwise our other dishes were simply ordinary...good eating  but nothing to rave home about. It's still worth a visit...service could be a tad faster  and I had to order the same drink twice...but just having this king of food available is nice. Inka Chicken  way up North is another Peruvian spot worthy of 5 stars.

The food was absolutely incredible! I had the Chupe(It was out of this world fantastic) and the Arroz Chaufa de Mariscos! Jazmine was so kind and gave great recommendations. I loved the atmosphere and wonderful service too! I am definitely coming back here with more friends next time. This is by far my favorite place I've eaten at in Austin!

Excelente! Wow  how flavorful! Had the veggie platter and it had all the things. All kinds of textures  and flavors  and temperatures  even salty and sweet. Great presentation - very impressed.Seating was fast and easy. Little hot and loud in there. Easy parking in a casual area. Outdoor seating available: will be back when its not so hot. Spent about $50 on two meals  app  drink  and tip. Lovely.

reviews.review: KILLER SPOT! Have been living in the area for over a year and had not even considered this place as an option. What a fool I was! We were craving Mexican (noticed the Tex-Mex direction) but it's definitely more Mex than Tex (70/30). In terms of the physical space  it's nothing special and a little dark inside (when sunny  might be a good option to eat outside). When it comes to food  their kitchen shines from the very second you get the complimentary house made chips and salsa. Can't think of better chips (not exaggerating) and their red salsa has a good addictive kick to it. We got the enchiladas and changed the sauce it comes with while opting for the light green sauce. The only interesting part of the beef enchilada was that we asked if it was shredded beef (and Dr was yes) but in reality it's ground beef  which is a huge difference in texture and blend when eaten in an enchilada. Having said that  the flavors were so so good  we didn't even bother to tell the waiter. Also got the Pambazo and can can confirm it's just as good as a good quality Pambazo from Mexico City or Guadalajara. We didn't get any drinks but from the tables around us  it looks like they also put love into their cocktails. One last comment: prices are great and will definitely come back in a few weeks.

I have been a devoted admirer of Vivo's for an extensive period  ever since their Manor Road establishment. They have consistently maintained their exceptional ability to craft delectable San Antonio Style Tex Mex cuisine. Whether you're seeking a delightful outing with your significant other  a fun night out with friends  a memorable family gathering  or simply a casual brunch or lunch  Vivo is a superb choice. The attire can range from casual to smart casual  accommodating various preferences. Moreover  their recently introduced patio  skillfully managed by Cenaida and her team  enhances the overall aesthetic appeal of the establishment.During our visits  I always strive to secure a table in Kelly's section. She is an exceptional server who ensures that every aspect of your dining experience is splendid  fulfilling all your Tex Mex desires. A light-hearted remark  but she truly works wonders! To commence the meal  I typically indulge in the El Trio  featuring a delectable combination of guacamole  frijoles  and queso  accompanied by a perfectly crafted margarita on the rocks. It is an exquisite combination. My personal favorites on the menu are the California Nachos and the Puffy Tacos. The California Nachos  featuring a medley of beans  cheese  and sprouts  are immensely satisfying. The half portion is always plentiful for me. As for the Puffy Tacos  they hold a cherished place in my family's hearts for many years  and I highly recommend trying them if you haven't already.The service at Vivo is consistently top-notch  ensuring a delightful dining experience. The cuisine is consistently scrumptious  leaving you with a satiated appetite and a contented heart.

I have eaten here several times. It is the closest restaurant to AFS Cinema so luckily the food is good in addition to conveniently located. My favorites are the veggie chalupas (light meal) and the verde enchiladas (filling). The modern part of the modern tex-mex seems to be the use of bean sprouts. Casual  cheery ambience with an amazing selection of potted plants. Great outdoor seating area. Friendly service.
We tried this place after a meeting. We had to drive around in order to find the location. Great food and appetizers.
Beef fajita mNachos are the bomb here I ordered a to go shrimp nacho and they gave me chips n dip to go I love it here

Vivo Tex Mex in Austin is a great spot for tasty Tex-Mex. We really enjoyed their fresh chips and spicy salsa. The flautas were flavorful  nicely topped with lettuce and sour cream. Service was good  and the ambiance was festive. All in all  a solid place for a casual weekend meal.

Haven't been to Vivo in years but it was close and offered reservations on Easter and from there I started thinking about their signature puffy taco! I'm here to say it was a good as I remembered! Despite the delicious sounding brunch menu  I opted for my timeless faves verdes chicken enchiladas with one puffy taco on the side and I loved them both. Eeeek. I'll def be back.We were a party of six and I really appreciated being seated quickly. Service was good and since we were in the patio  I can't really speak to the ambiance. Look forward to checking out the interior on my next visit.

I first ate at Vivo's at their Manor Road location. They were tasty then and they haven't failed me yet. The puffy tacos and trio appetizer are very good. And the cocktails are potent. I would take a picture of my food but I clean my plate too quickly. Can't wait to go back.

The puffy tacos  y'all. Still thinking about them today. I've loved Vivo since it's original home on Manor  and this iteration holds much of the same charm - plus parking! This spot is located in the Linc next to AFS.I caught the tail end of happy hour: 4-6pm M-F. You get $2 off beers  margs  and select half price apps and 2 for $6 tacos. Seemed like the margs had changed a bit since my last visit (they had more of an artificial sweet n sour mix vibe)  but the price is right and they're always strong. I think Vivo has some of the best salsa in town. It's spicy but tastes homemade and FLAVORFUL. I also love the cantina chips.I enjoyed the 1/2 macho nacho HH plate and HH spinach and mushroom quesadillas. They were great. The real star of the show was my puffy taco plate. There was so much shredded chicken and it was DELICIOUS and juicy. The corn tortilla was perfectly puffed and fried  and the rice and beans had great flavor as well. I love that you can have a great evening at Vivo without breaking the bank and leave happy. Service was attentive too!
Solid menu  consistently great quality. Bit of a wait for our order when crowded  but has never affected quality.

reviews.review: My husband and I love going to Pappasitos. It's consistently delicious  good service and good pricing. We always leave full and with left overs.Ambience is very casual but still highly recommend!

What use to be has gone here  what remains.... A extremely LOUD place that makes it difficult to not have to loud talk over the noise. Food has gone way down hill and is SO SALTY.... I had a headache from how much salt was on the food. If you ask me I'd pass on this place as the last time we went will be the LAST TIME! This papasitos use to be good and served up food that was edible... now they sling overpriced drinks and creat a menu that looks like a children's book to hide the crappy service  terrible food  and diminished quality of the over all experience. PASS ON THIS PLACE THERE ARE MUCH BEETER MEXICAN FOOD PLACES with better food  service  prices and you don't have to shout at your date or family members at your table.

Kitchen was _very_ slow today and some of the food wasn't as hot as it should have been. Service was inattentive for chips and drinks. This is not a restaurant which should take 40+ minutes from seating to food arriving. No explanation or acknowledgment of the delay. The tamales (on the appetizer menu) I ordered to come with the meal weren't hot. Otherwise the food was good but disappointing on this trip.

I had lunch today at Pappasito's on the way to the airport. Everything my friend and I ordered was delicious. Our bartender  Ethan was amazing. He went above and beyond. I just wished I lived here so I could visit more often. Great job!

The waitress was responsive and accommodating to our needs. We enjoyed our visit. The food was tasty!Fajitas were juicy and tender  for a family of 4 we still had leftovers. Pricey  but definitely worth every Penny!

I have to admit the staff was on point considering it was graduation weekend at UT. The wait was an hour and a half but took a little less time. I hate to go to restaurants when it's close to closing time but they we'e able to accommodate our party of six and stated they would stay until everyone was fed and satisfied. The food was delicious and the kitchen manager came out and apologized for some of the delays we encountered. All in all  everyone was well taken cared for on a busy stormy evening.

We go to this place because it's always consistent with their fajitas  and you definitely get a lot of bang for the buck  and the drinks are pretty good.The meats are great quality and  juicy and tender.Unfortunately our servers were short staffed and had to hustle  which they did well.

This was my first time at Pappasito's and I had such an amazing experience. Not only was the food delicious but all of the staff was super friendly  especially our server and the manager. The environment is very family oriented as large groups came to celebrate birthdays and couples were there for a date night. We got the beef fajitas and it exceeded my expectations. I normally don't like TexMex but I am a fan of Pappasito's

We absolutely love Pappasitos. As someone from Houston living in Austin I'm so happy there's a location here  just wish they'd make one in south austin! The queso and salsa is my favorite in town  as well as the beef fajitas. We also got the shrimp brochette this last time  and it's so delicious. Also recommend getting a frozen house margarita  yummy and strong.

Papasitos is absolutely my favorite Tex Mex restaurants. The chips are always fresh and salted. I came yesterday looking due the Mahi Mahi but they discontinued the dish!!!!! Pleassssssse bring it back and keep on menu. Hands down it was my favorite thing on the menu. The second best is the shrimp fajitas  the butter is the extra topper that sets it apart from any other fajitas. The shrimp is peeled and seasoned perfectly and the veggies. I have no complaints

reviews.review: The food is always delicious  and last night was no exception. I had a bowl of soup called Yuki Jang. It is a spicy beef soup. I wasn't able to eat all of the soup  but I ate all the ingredients! It was very good and a nice change of food for me. The service has improved since my last visit. The servers were nice. Additionally  the wait time was very minimal. In fact  after ordering  I had my food around 10 minutes. The price is a little expensive  but overall worth it. Stop by Chosen Galbi and try it yourself. I don't think you will be disappointed with the food!

I've read other negative reviews and they hit it right. I've been to Los Angeles Chosun Korean BBQ numerous of times  they're considered high end best quality Korean bbq and it shows it. I give that place 5 stars. I wanted Chosun in Austin TX to be as good as the one in LA  but it doesn't come close. The taste and presentation doesn't compare. I was disappointed in their lunch version of bulgoggi. It was cooked in a pan instead of flame grilled making the meat less flavorful and tough. Not to mention watery.This restaurant reminds me of hole in the wall cheap style Korean food.. I wouldn't call it Chosun. I didn't want to write negative review  but with the price they're charging  they should up their game.

One of the few Korean restaurants in Austin  my Korean friends all said it was one of the pricier places to go for KBBQ  one even mentioned he would take his parents there  which I assume they would approve of. I've been to Chosun twice in the last year.The first time  I got the soondubu jjigae (soft tofu soup)  this was pretty pricey compared to the ones I've had anywhere else. They also charged extra for a second bowl of rice  which were smaller portioned than other places. Everyone at the table split the galbi jjim  which came off as really sweet and with many fatty pieces.I went to Chosun this past weekend with friends. This time I opted for the yukgaejang. The stew was pretty good  price-wise it's a little less drastic than the difference I noticed for soondubu jjigae. They give an okay amount of banchan for the table. They did offer to refill but I'm not sure if we would've been charged it  since the extra charge was mentioned in the menu.Overall  I felt that the value is not quite there  and the extra charge for rice  and possible banchan  almost feels taboo. Servers are nice though!

Came here on a Friday for lunch.Looking at the menu  I thought the bento box is pretty pricey. They're in $18-19 range I believe.I ordered the Dwaeji Bulgogi bento box. It came with a good mix of selections. I was wishing that I'd get some banchan  but seems that they don't give it with lunch specials.I think the bento box was just ok  but service is fast and friendly!

One of the best Korean places in Austin.The menu is standard issue here.There is nothing here you can't get at 39 other places in town.What is at issue is the quality of the raw ingredients and the quality of the execution.A recent all-appetizers meal was truly all-star.Seafood pancake - a ho-hum dish in most places - positively sparkled.The trick? All sorts of exotic shellfish - including lots of the strange smaller shellfish that shows up in Korean seafood markets that Anglos almost never buy.And these were fresh and full of taste.But even the stuff we DO buy like the squid was of a higher order.The six or seven nuggets of squid in my pancake was some of the best squid I have had in Austin in years.(Standard practice in a Korean seafood pancake: you never get more than six or seven nuggets of anything - but there are a lot of different nugget types.)Mandoo (Dumplings) were also surprisingly good.Dirty little secret: A lot of the dumplings you get in Asian restaurants in the US come straight out of a freezer bag.There are a million commercial frozen dumpling vendors out there. (I think HMart sells stuff from nearly all of them.)Commercial dumplings vary from really excellent to tasteless lumps of stuff.Well either Chosun Galbi chooses an excellent vendor for their dumplings or the dumplings are homemade.Either way the dumplings were excellent and absolutely packed with flavor - even steamed which is usually a flavor-killing way to get your dumplings.* * *If you read the other reviews you see a lot of bad reviews mixed in with enthusiastic reviews like mine.The larger sampling of reviews tells a consistent story.a) Once upon a time  (like around 2016) service used to be really bad. There were also fights with a manager about prices and bills.Those complaints have evaporated since 2020.Probably a certain manager is no longer there.b) People complain a lot about the meat for barbecuing.I don't particularly like Korean BBQ - either for the work involved or for the prices which tend to be sky high. So I don't get excited about K-BBQ even in the marvelous places that people love.But there seems to be widespread agreement that Chosun Galbi is not where you want to do your barbecuing. There are other places in Austin with better base quality meat.However  my own personal opinion is that what makes Korean restaurants great are the meals the cook cooks for you and not the meals you make yourself.The meals that are prepared for you in the Chosun Galbi Kitchen are outstanding.I am sticking with five stars.

Lack luster flavors  bad portion sizes  and overpriced for what you get. I ordered the Yook Gae Jang  the broth seemed very watered down  not much beef  lots of leeks. My buddy ordered the Sul Lung Tang  also watered not  broth was not rich. My buddy's wife ordered the Bi Bim Bop  barely gave her any meat - Literally just vegetables and rice. It would have been an extra $4 for meat when they already skimped her on the meat. Slow service on top of the poor quality of food. Auto 20% tip for a group of 6 as well.
Awesome service and great food!! Jay was a great guy and thank you for the great amazing service and food! This is a must try!

This place was yummy! My sister was craving some Korean yum Mines's & decided to come here for lunch on a Wednesday evening. It was not busy! We were seated right away. Unfortunately  the servers did not really know their own menu  which was a bummer. One of the main questions was if the plates were "shareable" and they said no  but once we received our food  we realized we had way too much food! It was delicious  but it was just too much for 2 girls. - Price: on the pricey side- Food: delish!!- Parking: easy/not hard

Chosun is a Korean bbq place where you can bbq your own food but as for us we didn't chose to do that. We chose to have to kitchen prepare our food. I know. It's part of the experience but to each his own. Not much ambiance but it's all about the food here. We really love Korean food. We ordered jab chae which was clear noodle with vegetables. It was really good. We always order jab chae whenever we go to Korean. The jab chae give us the standard of the Korean food. So it's was right on. Also  got the yangnyum galbi which is Korean short ribs. Loved it. It was so good. The Bulgogi was so tender and very tasty. Really enjoyed this too. And lastly  we got the bi bim bob. Another staple for our Korean food. Mix it up  cut up the fried egg and it was so good. Loved all of it. Very good Korean food. So this was a really good Korean food place. Bbq yourself or have the kitchen cook it. Either way it's good. Great food. Great Korean food. Decent service cause they are so busy with a huge waiting line. So if you like Korean food and in Austin  give it a try. It's very good. We enjoyed it.
Great kbbq option! Solid traditional selections if you want the classic kbbq experience.
